input: Anne is green. Fiona is big. Gary is blue. Gary is green. Gary is nice. Gary is red. Harry is blue. Harry is green. Harry is quiet. Harry is red. Quiet things are green. Quiet, blue things are green. Blue, smart things are red. All nice things are smart. All green, big things are quiet. If Anne is red and Anne is blue then Anne is smart. All quiet things are smart. Quiet, smart things are blue. If something is big then it is green. Question: Fiona is red.?
output:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Anne : obj
constant Fiona : obj
constant Gary : obj
constant Harry : obj

constant Green : obj → Prop
constant Big : obj → Prop
constant Blue : obj → Prop
constant Nice : obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop
constant Quiet : obj → Prop
constant Smart : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Green Anne
axiom T2 : Big Fiona
axiom T3 : Blue Gary
axiom T4 : Green Gary
axiom T5 : Nice Gary
axiom T6 : Red Gary
axiom T7 : Blue Harry
axiom T8 : Green Harry
axiom T9 : Quiet Harry
axiom T10 : Red Harry

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x → Green x
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x ∧ Blue x → Green x
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Blue x ∧ Smart x → Red x
axiom R4 : ∀ x : obj, Nice x → Smart x
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Green x ∧ Big x → Quiet x
axiom R6 : Anne = Red Anne ∧ Blue Anne → Smart Anne
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x → Smart x
axiom R8 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x ∧ Smart x → Blue x
axiom R9 : ∀ x : obj, Big x → Green x

theorem fiona_is_red : Red Fiona :=
begin
  apply R3 Fiona,
  split,
  apply R8 Fiona,
  split,
  apply R5 Fiona,
  split,
  exact T2,
  apply R9,
  exact T2,
  apply R7 Fiona,
  apply R5 Fiona,
  split,
  exact T2,
  apply R9,
  exact T2,
end

-- The answer is True
